{
  "texts": [
    "Yet, recent work on multilingual language models 91, 92 holds the potential to democratize EWS for historically under-served communities, facilitating easier communication of warnings in multiple languages at minimal cost.",
    "The next frontier lies in spoken language, where radio, identified by UN Global Pulse as a powerful tool for social listening 93, can be leveraged by speech models supporting over 1000+ languages 94 as additional data, paving the way for user-centric EWS.",
    "AI is not a silver bullet to solve all problemsrather the usage of AI comes with its own challenges.",
    "In particular supervised ML, which seems most promising for EWS, suffers from problems with biases.",
    "Most prominently, supervised AI methods are particularly strong if the testing scenario is as close as possible to the training datathat is if there is no distribution shift between training and testing data 95."
  ]
}